Name: gmail
Description: Send and receive Gmail via SMTP/IMAP using 16-digit app password.
Version: 1.0

Overview:
This toolset provides Gmail email send and fetch capabilities using an app
password (16-digit). It supports attachments, HTML, search, and basic mailbox
management.

Commands:
- gmail_send
  Send an email via Gmail SMTP.
  Parameters:
  - to (array, required): Recipient list.
  - subject (string, required)
  - body (string, required)
  - html (string, optional)
  - cc (array, optional)
  - bcc (array, optional)
  - reply_to (string, optional)
  - from_email (string, optional): Defaults to env GMAIL_USER.
  - attachments (array, optional): File paths.
  - headers (object, optional): Extra headers.
  - smtp_host (string, optional): Default smtp.gmail.com.
  - smtp_port (integer, optional): Default 465.
  - timeout (integer, optional): Default 20.

- gmail_list_folders
  List Gmail folders/labels via IMAP.
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional): Defaults to env GMAIL_USER.
  - imap_host (string, optional): Default imap.gmail.com.
  - timeout (integer, optional): Default 20.

- gmail_fetch
  Fetch messages via IMAP.
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional)
  - folder (string, optional): Default INBOX.
  - query (string, optional): IMAP search query.
  - unseen_only (boolean, optional)
  - since (string, optional): YYYY-MM-DD
  - before (string, optional): YYYY-MM-DD
  - limit (integer, optional): Default 10.
  - mark_read (boolean, optional)
  - include_body (boolean, optional): Default true.
  - include_html (boolean, optional): Default false.
  - include_attachments (boolean, optional): Default false.
  - download_dir (string, optional): Save attachments to this dir.
  - imap_host (string, optional): Default imap.gmail.com.
  - timeout (integer, optional): Default 20.

- gmail_fetch_headers
  Fetch message headers only.
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional)
  - folder (string, optional)
  - query (string, optional)
  - limit (integer, optional)
  - imap_host (string, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)

- gmail_get_raw
  Fetch raw RFC822 message by id.
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional)
  - folder (string, optional)
  - msg_id (string, required)
  - imap_host (string, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)

- gmail_mark_read
  Mark a message as read.
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional)
  - folder (string, optional)
  - msg_id (string, required)
  - imap_host (string, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)

- gmail_mark_unread
  Mark a message as unread.
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional)
  - folder (string, optional)
  - msg_id (string, required)
  - imap_host (string, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)

- gmail_delete
  Delete a message (moves to Trash).
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional)
  - folder (string, optional)
  - msg_id (string, required)
  - imap_host (string, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)

- gmail_move
  Move a message to another folder/label.
  Parameters:
  - email (string, optional)
  - folder (string, optional)
  - msg_id (string, required)
  - target_folder (string, required)
  - imap_host (string, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)

Usage Examples:
- gmail_send to=["a@example.com"] subject="Hello" body="Hi" \
  app_password="xxxx xxxx xxxx xxxx"
- gmail_send_later send_at="2026-04-01T18:30:00Z" to=["a@example.com"] subject="Later" body="Hi"
- gmail_send_pending
- gmail_fetch unseen_only=true limit=5
- gmail_list_folders

Behavior Notes:
- Requires Gmail app password (16-digit) and Gmail IMAP enabled.
- Attachments are saved if download_dir is provided.
- Scheduled emails are stored locally under toolsf/gmail/tool/queue.

Dependencies:
- Python standard library (smtplib, imaplib, email)
- python-dotenv (optional) for loading .env
- gmail_send_later
  Schedule an email for later (stores locally if not due).
  Parameters:
  - send_at (string, required): ISO 8601 datetime.
  - to (array, required)
  - subject (string, required)
  - body (string, required)
  - html (string, optional)
  - cc (array, optional)
  - bcc (array, optional)
  - reply_to (string, optional)
  - from_email (string, optional)
  - attachments (array, optional)
  - headers (object, optional)
  - smtp_host (string, optional)
  - smtp_port (integer, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)

- gmail_send_pending
  Send any scheduled emails that are due.
  Parameters:
  - from_email (string, optional)
  - smtp_host (string, optional)
  - smtp_port (integer, optional)
  - timeout (integer, optional)
